      <description>Have you been thinking about writing a let&amp;#8217;s get back together letter to your ex? Here are a few tips of how to handle things if your ex has just ended things with you. The trick is to actually give permission for your ex to be free. Sounds weird, doesn&amp;#8217;t it, but this is actually...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a class="more-link" href="http://howtogetexbacktips.com/writing-a-letter-to-your-ex/what-should-your-write-in-a-get-back-together-letter/"&gt;Read the rest of this entry&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/how-to-get-ex-back-tips/How_To_Get_Ex_Back_Tips-What_Should_You_Write_In_A_Get_Back_Together_Letter.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Have you been thinking about writing a let&#8217;s get back together letter to your ex? Here are a few tips of how to handle things if your ex has just ended things with you. The trick is to actually give permission for your ex to be free. Sounds weird, doesn&#8217;t it, but this is actually just the first step in the overall plan to get your ex back. But you need to make the right moves at the right time to get your ex back for good this time. Visit <a href="http://howtogetexbacktips.com/making-up.php">This site</a> for the <em>next step</em> you must take in the plan to get your ex back for good.</strong></p>
<p><u>Should I Write A Get Back Together Letter?</u></p>
<p>It’s that moment we all dread, even if at times we’ve seen it coming; your soon-to-be ex tells you that your relationship is over. In this confused state you are often coping with the loss of the one you love whilst trying to work out how to get them back. Even though you are feeling anxious and miserable, try to refrain from contacting your ex asking questions about the break up &#8211; they need some space right now.</p>
<p>The most crucial time is immediately after you have broken up. What you say and do at this time can really affect your chances of getting your ex back.</p>
<p>First off, the very best thing you can do is to agree with your ex that breaking up is a good idea. Your ex will not be anticipating this type of reaction, as strange as it may seem to you. This response has been proved to be incredibly effective.</p>
<p>So you are beyond the point of giving your ex some space and have been constantly calling or texting them? Don&#8217;t worry, there is one thing you can do that will guarantee to redeem some of your behavior in the eyes of your lost love.</p>
<p>This requires a bit more effort on your part, but your worth can increase ten fold in the eyes of your ex. This is what you should do. Write them a short letter telling them that you have been giving things some thought and that the were right to want to break up. You will come across as accepting and calm which is much more appealing to them than being desperate and needy.</p>
<p>The letter must be very brief and the only thing you should say is that you agree with the break up. Just make sure you write an actual letter and not just text them or call them on the phone. Or worse, tell them face to face.</p>
<p>Do you wonder why this works much better than just a simple &#8220;let&#8217;s get back together&#8221; letter? Well, you&#8217;re actually complimenting your ex, by agreeing with them and letting them know in a very physical, real way that they have actually been heard. If you have been sending hundreds of text messages, or calling them constantly, another phone call or text won&#8217;t change things. A real, physical letter is different and means a lot more. But remember, it&#8217;s just the first step in the <a href="http://howtogetexbacktips.com/making-up.php"> overall plan </a>to get them back!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
